The paper deals with the definition and computation of higher inductive-inductive types, which are a type of dependent types. This falls under the category of logic and computation (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of syntactic logical relation translations, which is a technique used in programming languages and type theory (cs.PL). The paper also deals with the construction of initial algebras, which is a topic in category theory (cs.CT). The paper also discusses the use of equality constructors, which is a topic in homotopy type theory (cs.LOgic). Finally, the paper deals with the well-typed syntax of type theory, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.IT) and also discusses the use of conversion rules, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
